    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bolts, usually of steel, that hold overlapping sections of gutters to each other, and that attach the gutter to the eaves of a roof. For long nails or spikes used to secure gutters to the structure, use "gutter spikes."</Note_Text>
